tell you a fact.

00:02:14.230 --> 00:02:15.847
Many of you may
already know this.

00:02:19.010 --> 00:02:28.270
So I'll first tell you a
fact that any orientable two

00:02:28.270 --> 00:02:58.986
dimensional surface is
classified topologically

00:02:58.986 --> 00:03:05.960
by integer, which I will call h.

00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:08.723
So this h is called a genus.

00:03:16.090 --> 00:03:35.010
So heuristically, this genus
is equal to the number of holes

00:03:35.010 --> 00:03:36.020
a surface has.

00:03:40.890 --> 00:03:46.850
So for example, if
you have a plane,

00:03:46.850 --> 00:03:49.860
the plane topologically
is actually

00:03:49.860 --> 00:03:52.470
equivalent to a
sphere, so when I

00:03:52.470 --> 00:03:55.380
draw a sphere,
that means a plane,

00:03:55.380 --> 00:03:57.180
because if you
identify the point

00:03:57.180 --> 00:04:01.770
on the plane of the infinity,
then it becomes a sphere.

00:04:01.770 --> 00:04:04.590
So topologically, a plane is
no different from a sphere.

00:04:04.590 --> 00:04:07.900
So this genus 0.

00:04:07.900 --> 00:04:08.723
So this is plane.

00:04:12.340 --> 00:04:13.330
So h is equal to 0.

00:04:16.290 --> 00:04:26.920
And then for torus,
then there's one hole,

00:04:26.920 --> 00:04:27.980
and this is just genus 1.

00:04:30.720 --> 00:04:33.560
So this is torus.

00:04:33.560 --> 00:04:40.995
You can also draw surfaces
with as many holes as you want.

00:04:40.995 --> 00:04:42.952
So this is surface
with two holes.

00:04:46.950 --> 00:04:50.800
A surface with two holes,
and so this is genius 2.

00:04:55.310 --> 00:04:59.050
So the remarkable thing
is that this actually

00:04:59.050 --> 00:05:03.296
classifies the topology of
all two-dimensional surfaces.

00:05:06.600 --> 00:05:12.090
And this so-called
topological invariant,

00:05:12.090 --> 00:05:18.930
there's a topological number
a so-called Euler number,

00:05:18.930 --> 00:05:25.710
which is defined to be Chi
is equal to 2 minus 2h.

00:05:25.710 --> 00:05:32.720
So if h labels the
topology, and so the Chi

00:05:32.720 --> 00:05:35.010
is related to h in this way.

00:05:35.010 --> 00:05:39.865
So any two surfaces
with the same topology

00:05:39.865 --> 00:05:43.330
will have the same Chi, because
if they have the same h,

00:05:43.330 --> 00:05:44.520
they have the same Chi.

00:05:44.520 --> 00:05:48.385
So Chi is what we call the
topological invariants.

00:05:51.550 --> 00:05:54.790
So this is just a
mathematical fact.

