00:12:58.550 --> 00:13:02.496
Again, we have been only talking
about the vacuum diagram.

00:13:02.496 --> 00:13:07.810
Vacuum diagram means the
diagram has no external lags,

00:13:07.810 --> 00:13:09.570
has the full independence.

00:13:09.570 --> 00:13:13.140
So from here, we
immediately conclude

00:13:13.140 --> 00:13:25.965
that the vacuum diagram has
the following, g squared

00:13:25.965 --> 00:13:26.590
and dependence.

00:13:32.090 --> 00:13:34.810
So g squared is just
the carpeting constant.

00:13:34.810 --> 00:13:39.990
So remember, each propagator
is proportional to g squared

00:13:39.990 --> 00:13:47.233
and that each vertex
is one over g squared.

00:13:49.950 --> 00:13:53.210
Just from there.

00:13:53.210 --> 00:13:55.940
So let's just take an
arbitrary vacuum diagram.

00:13:55.940 --> 00:14:02.470
Let me call this amplitude
to be A. And A should

00:14:02.470 --> 00:14:05.760
be proportional to g
squared to the power

00:14:05.760 --> 00:14:21.620
E. E should be the
number of propagators,

00:14:21.620 --> 00:14:24.450
because each propagator gives
you a factor of g squared.

00:14:26.970 --> 00:14:33.630
And also minus V.
And V is the number

00:14:33.630 --> 00:14:38.130
of vertices below to
the number of vertices.

00:14:38.130 --> 00:14:40.970
And each vertex gives
you one over g squared,

00:14:40.970 --> 00:14:45.890
so that should
give you E minus V.

00:14:45.890 --> 00:14:50.530
And then we just multiply
N to the power of F,

00:14:50.530 --> 00:14:52.010
and F is the number of faces.

00:15:03.810 --> 00:15:07.690
So without doing
any calculation,

00:15:07.690 --> 00:15:15.222
so this has essentially
characterized the N and the g

00:15:15.222 --> 00:15:17.222
and the accompanying
dependents of any diagrams.

